  "prompt": "What's the best residential ISP in San Francisco?",
  "response": "Choosing the best residential ISP in San Francisco can depend on various factors such as speed, reliability, cost, and customer service. As of the latest information available, here are some of the most highly rated ISPs in San Francisco:\n\n1. **Xfinity by Comcast**: Known for its high-speed internet options, Xfinity offers a wide range of plans and is known for its extensive coverage and reliability. They also have a good bundle of services including TV and phone.\n\n2. **AT&T**: AT&T provides high-speed fiber-optic internet in many areas of San Francisco. Their fiber plans are particularly noted for fast speeds and reliability. They also offer DSL options where fiber isn\u2019t available.\n\n3. **Sonic**: Sonic is a local ISP that has built a reputation for strong customer service and fairly priced internet plans. They offer DSL and fiber services and are known for being customer-friendly.\n\n4. **Webpass (a Google Fiber company)**: Webpass offers high-speed internet via fiber and is known for quick installation and excellent customer service. Their service, however, is mostly available in select apartment buildings and commercial areas.\n\n5. **Wave Broadband/EarthLink**: These ISPs offer competitive speeds and prices for internet services. They also provide cable internet options with wide coverage.\n\nWhen choosing an ISP, it\u2019s essential to check the specific coverage and services available at your address, read current customer reviews, and compare plans based on your usage needs. Additionally, you may want to consider their contractual terms, data caps, equipment fees, and promotional pricing.",
